{
  "texts": [
    "b Macroporous metals have large convex/concave surfaces and an open framework that enables both light and MPs to penetrate deep into the metal network.",
    "Texturing the metal surfaces with mesopores enables light to excite intense local electric field intensities that correspond to strong SERS enhancements in adjacent molecules.",
    "Coating the surface with hydrophobic groups facilitates the trapping of MPs versus small water-soluble molecules.",
    "c MPs in environmental samples are relatively dilute compared to other forms of organic and inorganic matter thus, preconcentration and pretreatment methods are typically necessary before analytical measurement.",
    "Our macroporous metals are designed to recruit MPs from aqueous solution and prevent biofouling."
  ]
}